What programming paradigm is more suitable for designing an intricate social network application? Object-Oriented Programming (OOP) and Procedural Programming represent two different approaches to structuring and implementing software programs. Considering an intricate social network application, which involves complex data structures, user interactions, relationships, and a rich set of features, it is evident that OOP would be a more suitable choice for its robust object-oriented design, modularity, and encapsulation capabilities.

